<doc id="1186181" wikidata="Q3434623" url="?curid=1186181" title="Robert Bouchard">
<text>Robert Bouchard (born March 30, 1943) is a Canadian politician. Born in Saint-Émond, Quebec, Bouchard represented the riding of Chicoutimi—Le Fjord in the House of Commons of Canada from 2004 to 2011 as a member of the Bloc Québécois.

Bouchard served as the Bloc Québécois critic for National Revenue.

