<doc id="1186447" wikidata="Q2297976" url="?curid=1186447" title="Algerian Party for Democracy and Socialism">
<text>The Algerian Party for Democracy and Socialism (, PADS) is a Communist party in Algeria. When in 1993, during the Algerian Civil War, Ettehadi was realigned as a democratic movement resisting Islamism, the Marxist–Leninist wing split apart under the leadership of Abdelhamid Benzine to retain its Marxist–Leninist legacy.

PADS publishes the newspaper &quot;Le Lien des Ouvriers et Paysans&quot; (The Link of the Workers and Peasants).

