<doc id="1186449" wikidata="Q7959408" url="?curid=1186449" title="Wafaa (party)">
<text>The Wafaa is an illegal political party in Algeria. The party was founded by Ahmed Taleb Ibrahimi, son of Bashir al-Ibrahimi and several times a minister in the Boumédiène and Bendjedid eras. It was banned in 2000 for alleged links to the outlawed Islamic Salvation Front (FIS).

